On February 27, 2018, several nominations and appointments were made. These include an individual to be a Member of the Board of Directors of the Federal Prison Industries as the Department of Defense Representative, an individual to be a Member of the President's Board of Advisors on Historically Black Colleges and Universities and upon appointment designate him Chairman, an individual to be a Member of the Frederick Douglass Bicentennial Commission as the Maryland Governor's Representative, and several individuals to be Members of the board of visitors to the United States Naval Academy.